{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dace26b5-1e38-456a-bf78-de055ba4c5a8","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n**1. Update packages in your `.csproj`:**\n- Upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **5.0.0+** (adds Microsoft.Testing.Platform support)\n- Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n- Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` (optional, for TRx reports)\n\n**2. Enable the new platform in your `.csproj`:**\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests with:**\n```bash\ndotnet run -- --help        # to see new CLI options\ndotnet test                 # still works as before\n```\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- Each test project becomes a standalone executable (`OutputType=Exe`)\n- CLI args change (e.g., `--filter` → `--treenode-filter`)\n- `.runsettings` files are still supported but some VSTest-specific settings may not apply\n- Use `--report-trx` instead of `--logger trx` if you added the TRx package","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aa7f503f-446c-4920-ba74-62229c836d2f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to explore any codebase. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nKey steps for migrating NUnit from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. Update NUnit3TestAdapter to version 5.0+ (which supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform)\n2. Replace Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk with Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n3. Add the appropriate entry point\n4. Update project file settings\n\nLet me give a concise but accurate answer.","outputTokens":439,"requestId":"CFC8:2D9C3A:6015A98:6B41E58:69EC0DF0"},"id":"9915ae2b-4707-4676-8ff7-3740199a2bb0","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:42:35.511Z","parentId":"7e419860-e07e-46d6-bcec-18b3bd81d70d"}
